    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="199"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/30634</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Assistant to the President’s Military Aide</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hammond</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Assistant Chief of the Division of
                        European Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hickerson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-09">August 9,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for Mr. Hickerson</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The following message from the President was received in the <gloss
                        target="#t_White1">White</gloss> House Map Room during the night: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Proposed Canadian release is approved as to text and procedure.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0524" n="410" xml:id="pg_410"/>
                <p>The duty officer in the office of the Secretary of State was notified August 8th
                    at 2330.<note n="1" xml:id="d199fn1">i.e., 11:30 p.m. This memorandum bears the
                        following manuscript endorsement by Hickerson: “Telephoned to Mr. Atherton,
                        Am. Legation, Ottawa 9:45 a.m. Aug. 9 J[ohn] D H[iekerson]”.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chester Hammond</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Lt. Colonel, General Staff</hi>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Asst. to the Military Aide</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
